<h2 id="the-sections-below-were-used-when-the-class-was-2-hours-long">The sections below were used when the class was 2 hours long.</h2>

<h3 id="pair-practice">Pair Practice</h3>

<p>Using <a href="https://github.com/turingschool-examples/feel-good-bot">Feel Good Bot</a>:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Refactor the site navigation into a partial.</li>
  <li>Create a helper for the following:
    <ul>
      <li>A image tag helper that takes a file name and creates an HTML image tag prefixed by <code class="highlighter-rouge">images/</code></li>
      <li>A stylesheet helper that takes the name of a CSS file and creates a <code class="highlighter-rouge">link</code> tag</li>
      <li>A <code class="highlighter-rouge">home_url</code> helper that returns the <code class="highlighter-rouge">url</code> helper for the home page (in this case thatâ€™s <code class="highlighter-rouge">/</code>)</li>
      <li>A <code class="highlighter-rouge">mean_url</code> helper that returns the <code class="highlighter-rouge">url</code> helper for the mean robot page (in this case thatâ€™s <code class="highlighter-rouge">/mean</code>)</li>
      <li>A <code class="highlighter-rouge">robots_url</code> helper that returns the <code class="highlighter-rouge">url</code> helper for the mean robot page (in this case thatâ€™s <code class="highlighter-rouge">/robots</code>)</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

<h3 id="reflections">Reflections</h3>

<h4 id="taught-by-steve-2014-11-04">Taught by Steve (2014-11-04)</h4>

<p>The code along went well, but I think it could stand to be shortened. Iâ€™d like to actually take an old Clone Wars project and begin to refactor it with them. I think that would more useful than the super granular code-along.</p>

<p>Some students thought the pair practice tasks were a bit contrived. Again, I might take an old Clone Wars or Idea Box and have them refactor it instead.</p>

